      <title>A Coding-Agent-Friendly Environment Is Friendly to Humans Too: ghq √ó gwq √ó fzf</title>
      <link>https://shunk031.me/post/ghq-gwq-fzf-worktree/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 16 Jan 2026 23:45:26 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://shunk031.me/post/ghq-gwq-fzf-worktree/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;As your number of repositories grows through &lt;code&gt;git clone&lt;/code&gt;, for both work and personal projects, it becomes harder to remember &lt;strong&gt;where&lt;/strong&gt; you cloned things and &lt;strong&gt;which directory&lt;/strong&gt; you‚Äôre currently working in. You end up wasting time on &lt;code&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt; and shell completion. On top of that, once you start creating branches for development or checking out other branches to review Pull Requests, the overhead of switching branches and managing stashes just keeps increasing. I often mess up branch switches, run into conflicts, or almost lose my changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These problems become even more visible once you start using coding agents like &lt;strong&gt;Claude Code&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Codex&lt;/strong&gt;. The more tasks you run in parallel, the more likely things are to collide if you only have a single working directory. And of course, you want to unleash your coding agents as much as possible üòÑ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this article, I‚Äôll show how combining the following three tools can significantly improve your daily development workflow. And yes‚Äîplease do use coding agents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/x-motemen/ghq&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ghq&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to standardize where repositories are cloned (so things don‚Äôt fall apart as they grow)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/d-kuro/gwq&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;gwq&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to make git worktree operations painless (parallel work becomes the default)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/junegunn/fzf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;fzf&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to minimize directory hopping (list ‚Üí fuzzy search ‚Üí instant jump)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


